      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2. Analyst competency addressed through SQA and internal peer review process.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment not required at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Analyst qualifications documented in SQA package (10+ years CFD experience, two independent peer reviews of all simulation setups). Formal use error quantification deferred. Gradation 1 acceptable at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The chosen turbulence model and hemolysis damage model must be justified for the flow regime. Sensitivity to model form choices must be evaluated.",
      "rationale": "k-omega SST turbulence model selected based on published benchmarks for confined rotating flows (Reynolds number 10^4–10^5). Hemolysis damage model: Giersiepen-Wurzinger power law with modified Lagrangian exposure time tracking. Turbulence model sensitivity study (k-omega SST vs. realizable k-epsilon): NIH difference < 2% at all operating points. Model form uncertainty estimated at 9.3% (dominant uncertainty source, as expected). Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Key model inputs (fluid properties, boundary conditions, geometric parameters) must be characterized with documented uncertainty. Sensitivity of QoI to input uncertainty must be assessed.",
      "rationale": "Input uncertainty characterization: inlet velocity (±2% at 95% CI), fluid viscosity (±3% at 95% CI), rotational speed (±0.2% at 95% CI), geometric dimensions (±0.05 mm manufacturing tolerance). One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis identifies viscosity and inlet velocity as dominant inputs. Monte Carlo propagation (1000 samples) yields NIH 95% CI half-width of ±4.1%. All inputs documented in simulation data management plan. Gradation 2 met."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
