    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels at Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 requirements per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. The dominant uncertainty source (model form, 9.3%) is within acceptable bounds for a Class II device at this risk level. Validation results across five operating points demonstrate conservative hemolysis prediction (mean RH = 0.87). The geometric sensitivity response surface (R² = 0.96) provides adequate coverage of the manufacturing tolerance space. The CFD model is accepted as credible for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the CPB COU.",
